{
  "texts": [
    "This method reliably detects unitary excitatory and inhibitory synaptic connectivity with its submillisecond and subthreshold resolution [168].",
    "Increasing the number of simultaneously recorded neurons can considerably increase the number of probed synaptic connections and generate larger sample sizes from fewer experiments.",
    "For example, if the number of simultaneously patched neurons reaches eight in single slices, 56 potential connections will be tested.",
    "It is important to achieve relatively high throughput due to the limited availability of primate samples.",
    "By using multicell whole-cell patch-clamp recordings, simultaneous recording of multiple neurons becomes possible."
  ]
}